 "cells": [
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Project 8 — Local Blog-to-Thread Converter\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Repurpose Long-Form Content into Threads, Posts, and Emails\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Goal:** Transform a blog article into a Twitter/X thread, LinkedIn post,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"newsletter email, and TL;DR — learning controlled content transformation.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Stack:** Ollama · LangChain · Jupyter\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### What You'll Learn\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Format-constrained generation\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Length control for platforms\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Tone adaptation\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Content preservation across formats\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "     \"# !pip install -q langchain langchain-ollama langchain-core\"\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   {\n",
    "    \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "    \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "    \"source\": [\n",
    "     \"## Step 1 — Configure LLM\"\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   {\n",
    "    \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "    \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "    \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "    \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "    \"source\": [\n",
    "     \"import requests\\n\",\n",
    "     \"from langchain_ollama import ChatOllama\\n\",\n",
    "     \"from langchain_core.prompts import ChatPromptTemplate\\n\",\n",
    "     \"from langchain_core.output_parsers import StrOutputParser\\n\",\n",
    "     \"\\n\",\n",
    "     \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "     \"    r = requests.get(\\\"http://localhost:11434/api/tags\\\", timeout=5)\\n\",\n",
    "     \"    print(f\\\"Ollama running — {len(r.json().get('models', []))} models\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "     \"except: print(\\\"Start Ollama first!\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "     \"\\n\",\n",
    "     \"llm = ChatOllama(model=\\\"qwen3:8b\\\", temperature=0.5)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"blog_post = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Why RAG Beats Fine-Tuning for Most Enterprise Use Cases\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The debate between Retrieval-Augmented Generation and fine-tuning has evolved\\n\",\n",
    "    \"significantly. While fine-tuning creates specialized models, RAG offers advantages\\n\",\n",
    "    \"that make it the better default choice for most enterprise applications.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Cost Efficiency**: Fine-tuning requires curating datasets, running training jobs,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"and maintaining multiple model versions. RAG needs only a vector database and an\\n\",\n",
    "    \"embedding pipeline — often 10x cheaper to set up and maintain.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Data Freshness**: Fine-tuned models are frozen at training time. When your company\\n\",\n",
    "    \"policies, products, or documentation change, you need to retrain. RAG systems\\n\",\n",
    "    \"update instantly — just re-embed the new documents.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Transparency**: RAG provides source citations. Users can verify answers against\\n\",\n",
    "    \"the original documents. Fine-tuned models are black boxes — you can't trace where\\n\",\n",
    "    \"an answer came from.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Composability**: A single RAG system can serve multiple domains by swapping\\n\",\n",
    "    \"document collections. Fine-tuning requires separate models for each domain.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**When Fine-Tuning Wins**: Style/tone adaptation, consistent formatting requirements,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"and high-throughput latency-sensitive applications where retrieval adds overhead.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The pragmatic approach: Start with RAG, measure gaps, and fine-tune only when\\n\",\n",
    "    \"you have clear evidence that RAG alone can't meet your quality bar.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Blog post loaded: {len(blog_post)} chars\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Step 2 — Convert to Twitter/X Thread\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"thread_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"system\\\", \\\"\\\"\\\"Convert blog posts into engaging Twitter/X threads. Rules:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- First tweet: hook that makes people want to read more\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- 5-10 tweets total, each under 280 characters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Use numbered format (1/, 2/, etc.)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Include a mix of insights, data points, and opinions\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- End with a takeaway or call to action\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Use line breaks for readability\\\"\\\"\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"human\\\", \\\"Convert this blog post to a Twitter thread:\\\\n\\\\n{blog}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"thread_chain = thread_prompt | llm | StrOutputParser()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"thread = thread_chain.invoke({\\\"blog\\\": blog_post})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"TWITTER THREAD:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(thread)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Step 3 — Convert to LinkedIn Post\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"linkedin_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"system\\\", \\\"\\\"\\\"Convert blog posts into LinkedIn posts. Rules:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Opening hook (first line visible before 'See more')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Professional but conversational tone\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Use bullet points or numbered lists\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Include a personal insight or opinion\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- End with a question to drive engagement\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- 150-300 words\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Add relevant hashtags\\\"\\\"\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"human\\\", \\\"Convert this to a LinkedIn post:\\\\n\\\\n{blog}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"linkedin_chain = linkedin_prompt | llm | StrOutputParser()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"post = linkedin_chain.invoke({\\\"blog\\\": blog_post})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"LINKEDIN POST:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(post)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Step 4 — Convert to Newsletter Email\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"email_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"system\\\", \\\"\\\"\\\"Convert blog posts into newsletter emails. Rules:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Compelling subject line\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Personal greeting\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- TL;DR at the top (3 bullets)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Expanded discussion with examples\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Clear CTA (reply, share, or link)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Casual but authoritative tone\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Under 500 words\\\"\\\"\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"human\\\", \\\"Convert this blog to a newsletter email:\\\\n\\\\n{blog}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"email_chain = email_prompt | llm | StrOutputParser()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"newsletter = email_chain.invoke({\\\"blog\\\": blog_post})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"NEWSLETTER EMAIL:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(newsletter)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Step 5 — All-Formats Pipeline\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"formats = {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"twitter_thread\\\": thread_chain,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"linkedin_post\\\": linkedin_chain,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"newsletter_email\\\": email_chain,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=== CONTENT REPURPOSING PIPELINE ===\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for fmt_name, chain in formats.items():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"\\\\n{'='*60}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"FORMAT: {fmt_name}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print('='*60)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    result = chain.invoke({\\\"blog\\\": blog_post})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(result[:300] + \\\"...\\\" if len(result) > 300 else result)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"\\\\n[{len(result)} chars generated]\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## What You Learned\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Platform-specific content adaptation** (Twitter, LinkedIn, Email)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Tone and format constraints** via system prompts\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Batch content repurposing** pipeline\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Use your own blog post and repurpose it\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Add a Reddit post format\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Compare output quality across formats\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"*Next: **09 — Local Study Notes Generator***\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
